<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-59-0358 </DOCNO><TEXT>It is shown how one can build an off-diagonal off-shell non-perturbatives-d transition with the PCAC hypothesis after chiral symmetry breakingin QCD. The resulting effective Hamiltonian correctly reproduces almostthe whole (up to 80%) of the asub(1/2)(K/sup 0/ -andgt; 2{pi}) amplitude andtherefore demonstrates the importance of long-distance contributionsto the {Delta}I = 1/2 rule.</TEXT></DOC>